me.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Bleachers.-Credit-Alex-Lockett-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Bleachers.-Credit-Alex-Lockett-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Bleachers.-Credit-Alex-Lockett-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="/artists/bleachers">Bleachers</a>分享了他们的最新单曲“Alma Mater”，并宣布了他们的新同名专辑“Bleachers”。</p><ul class="post-content-read-more"><li><strong>阅读更多： <a href="https://www.nme.com/big-reads/bleachers-jack-antonoff-cover-interview-2021-take-the-sadness-out-of-saturday-night-3006942">Bleachers：“这张专辑是关于想要保持快乐，而不是理解为什么你不能”</a></strong></li></ul><p> 《Alma Mater》是杰克·安东诺夫及其合作者即将发行的专辑中发行的第二首歌曲。这是继九月初发行的主打单曲《 <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/bleachers-return-with-new-single-modern-girl-3501228">Modern Girl</a> 》之后的作品。这首歌是由<a href="/artists/lana-del-rey">Lana Del Rey</a>共同创作的，她在歌曲的中间唱着<em>“I&#39;ll make it darker”</em> 。</p><p>这首歌节奏较慢，有号角旋律，与之前发行的主打单曲完全相反，乐队分享了另一首感觉良好的歌曲，带有明亮的美式节拍和朗朗上口的歌词，内容是“出去摇晃屁股”。 </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="母校" width="696" height="522" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/2r_QeXlPHOM?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p>这两首歌曲都将出现在乐队的第四张录音室专辑“Bleachers”中。一份新闻稿将这张唱片描述为“安东诺夫对现代生活中奇异的感官矛盾、他在文化中的地位以及他所关心的事物的独特新泽西诠释。从声音上来说，它是悲伤的，也是快乐的，它是适合在高速公路上开车、适合哭泣、适合在婚礼上跳舞的音乐。”</p><p> 《Bleachers》定于 3 月 8 日发行。这也标志着乐队在新厂牌 Dirty Hit 下首次发行完整专辑。 <a href="https://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=001mUQMNZSQ02AJrW3yyUtaleL6-nHAeFPKNhlskY6lVq7fer16uSgqWXsgAa_a8gc-o2-nHfkveTBEB-SAKqev3tmpe0xqLDimm4kX7mQgEYvcRuB8G6k0njPAxCb_ewcoDx8SMUUyusdcxMgxTGc2kA==&amp;c=Li3p8rAXOSSEVqUwQzgpnatSpx2LdwEgadcxDR-76WKmqfpELwiM5Q==&amp;ch=7-oJVSdf8UF3i4FfqTwixSUsDOOoi6PoigJMtw4f7LNqZmbeZWeScA==" target="_blank" rel="noopener">在此</a>预订专辑。</p><p> Antonoff and Co. 还宣布将于 2024 年初在英国举办一系列头条演出，以庆祝专辑的发行。 11 月 21 日星期二下午 4 点之前从<a href="https://store.dirtyhit.co.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Dirty Hit 商店</a>预购 LP 的粉丝将获得门票预售。预售将于 11 月 22 日星期三上午 10 点（格林威治标准时间）开始。一般门票销售将于 11 月 24 日星期五上午 10 点（格林威治标准时间）开始。 <a href="https://ticketmaster-uk.tm7559.net/c/2862475/431519/7559?sharedid=NME&amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ticketmaster.co.uk%2Fbleachers-tickets%2Fartist%2F1965170" target="_blank" rel="noopener">请访问此处</a>获取门票，并<a href="https://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=001mUQMNZSQ02AJrW3yyUtaleL6-nHAeFPKNhlskY6lVq7fer16uSgqWYbs1P37iNBbUaDsQUa9NfIHkWHJ7KW5365xj4kiHvl8REodP47yUEmDQOdZDzB6LRRVa9DF6fkBwCSlpMWzK3QXbf1vVH_ed7TeJSi3Rpjy&amp;c=Li3p8rAXOSSEVqUwQzgpnatSpx2LdwEgadcxDR-76WKmqfpELwiM5Q==&amp;ch=7-oJVSdf8UF3i4FfqTwixSUsDOOoi6PoigJMtw4f7LNqZmbeZWeScA==" target="_blank" rel="noopener">访问此处</a>了解更多信息。</p><p> <strong>Bleachers UK 2024 年巡演日期为：</strong></p><p> <strong>2024 年 3 月</strong><br /><strong>19 – 伦敦，O2 论坛肯特镇</strong><br /><strong>22 - 曼彻斯特，O2 Ritz</strong><br /> <strong>23 – 伯明翰，O2 研究所</strong><br /><strong>25 – 格拉斯哥，SWG3 镀锌机</strong></p><figure id="attachment_3540266" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3540266" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3540266" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Bleachers-album-artwork.-Credit-Alex-Lockett.jpg" alt="《Bleachers》专辑封面。图片来源：亚历克斯·洛克特" width="2000" height="2000" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Bleachers-album-artwork.-Credit-Alex-Lockett.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Bleachers-album-artwork.-Credit-Alex-Lockett-150x150.jpg 150w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Bleachers-album-artwork.-Credit-Alex-Lockett-400x400.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Bleachers-album-artwork.-Credit-Alex-Lockett-800x800.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Bleachers-album-artwork.-Credit-Alex-Lockett-696x696.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Bleachers-album-artwork.-Credit-Alex-Lockett-1392x1392.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Bleachers-album-artwork.-Credit-Alex-Lockett-1068x1068.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3540266" class="wp-caption-text"> 《Bleachers》专辑封面。图片来源：亚历克斯·洛克特</figcaption></figure><p><strong>“Bleachers”曲目列表是：</strong></p><p> <strong>1.“我准时”</strong><br /> <strong>2.《摩登女郎》</strong><br /> <strong>3.《耶稣死了》</strong><br /> <strong>4.《在你之前的我》</strong><br /> <strong>5.《母校》</strong><br /> <strong>6.“小动作”</strong><br /> <strong>7.“伊西莫”</strong><br /> <strong>8.《今天醒来》</strong><br /> <strong>9.“自尊”</strong><br /> <strong>10.“嘿乔”</strong><br /> <strong>11.《午夜后给我打电话》</strong><br /> <strong>12.“我们会永远认识彼此”</strong><br /> <strong>13.《平凡的天堂》</strong><br /> <strong>14.《侍者》</strong></p><p>早在八月， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/jack-antonoff-signs-with-dirty-hit-announces-new-venture-with-the-1975-manager-jamie-oborne-3486106">Bleachers 就宣布他们将由 Jamie Oborne 管理，并与后者的独立厂牌 Dirty Hit 签约。</a>该品牌还拥有 The 1975、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/rina-sawayama">Rina Sawayama</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/wolf-alice">Wolf Alice</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/beabadoobee">Beabadoobee</a>等歌手。</p><p>安东诺夫还与经理人和音乐大亨联手成立了一家新的合资企业，前者还与环球音乐出版集团签署了全球协议。 The agreement sees him move from Sony to stay with his longtime publishing A&amp;R Jennifer Knoepfle, who, as reported by <em>Variety</em> , joined UMPG last fall as executive vice president and co-head of A&amp;R.</p><p> “Very proud to be working with Jamie and his entire team – we&#39;ve known each other for some time now and our connection has deeply inspired me,” said Antonoff in a statement. “Have loved everything he has been creating from afar and love the perspective he has on what I do.” </p><figure id="attachment_3540271" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3540271" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3540271" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Bleachers.-Credit-Alex-Lockett-1.jpg" alt="Bleachers. Credit: Alex Lockett" width="2000" height="1626" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Bleachers.-Credit-Alex-Lockett-1.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Bleachers.-Credit-Alex-Lockett-1-400x325.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Bleachers.-Credit-Alex-Lockett-1-800x650.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Bleachers.-Credit-Alex-Lockett-1-696x566.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Bleachers.-Credit-Alex-Lockett-1-1392x1132.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Bleachers.-Credit-Alex-Lockett-1-1068x868.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3540271" class="wp-caption-text"> Bleachers. Credit: Alex Lockett</figcaption></figure><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/bleachers-take-the-sadness-out-of-saturday-night-review-riotous-and-reflective-third-album-3006067">In a four-star review of their 2021 LP &#39;Take The Sadness Out Of Yesterday&#39;</a> , <em>NME</em> shared: “The record captures that sentiment in many forms – from the aftermath of Antonoff&#39;s 2018 break-up with actor-director Lena Dunham, the feeling of wanting to break free from his native New Jersey, the intense longing to play with his band when pandemic restrictions made it impossible.”</p><p> They continued: “Bleachers&#39; past releases might have dealt in the dark moments of life – loss, death and grieving among them – but they did so in a way that felt like you were exorcising your own ghosts by singing along. There are glimpses of that here, but also moments that leave you ruminating on your own need for escape, to run away from – or towards – something. It might not leave you feeling as euphoric as what&#39;s come before, but its lingering sensation is a testament to the power of Antonoff&#39;s immersive songwriting.”</p